      "place_type": "Railway company",
      "description": "The Midland Railway was one of Britain's major Victorian railway companies. Samuel Waite Johnson of 27 Lenton Road served as its Chief Mechanical Engineer. His most celebrated designs include the Midland Single (the 'Spinner'), elegant single-driver express locomotives with 7-foot driving wheels that became icons of Victorian railway engineering.",
